        <article style="font-size:20px">Sunday night December 22, 2018, suddenly residents came to the Al Furqon Mosque Da'wah Council in the Anyer Beach Area. They apparently ran away from the tsunami. This time the tsunami hit the western part of Java Island and southern Sumatra Island.<br><br>The last update on Wednesday afternoon, data from BNPB (National Disaster Management Agency) recorded 430 people died, 1,495 injured, 159 people missing and 21,991 displaced. The emergency response period for Pandeglang Regency is set to 4 January 2018. Meanwhile, for South Lampung it is set to 29 December 2018.<br><br>Affected areas include Pandeglang, Serang, and South Lampung Districts. The worst is residential and tourist areas on Tanjung Lesung Beach, Sumur Beach, Teluk Lada Beach, Panimbang Beach, and Carita Beach.<br><br>The unpredictable tsunami became a speck of grief on the final sheet of 2018. Even when this high-energy water swept the coast of Banten and South Lampung instead of just being called high waves. "Keep calm!" Unfortunately, this is not an ordinary high wave. This is more awesome than agile waves on a full moon.<br><br>Since that night, Saturday (12/22) the Da'wah Board of Education and Training Center of Al-Anshor, Anyer, Serang, Banten was filled with hundreds of refugees. They were so afraid of the roar of Anak Krakatau who 'never stopped threatening the tsunami.<br><br>Not only materially with distributing basic necessities and various other logistics, Laznas Da'wah Council also provides free mobile health services, Happy School of My Heart, the establishment of Public Kitchens, Sadaqah Makan Rakyat (Semarak), reciting the Kafilah of Lovers of the Qur'an, action clean the posts, takziah, religious prayer with local residents, synergize with foreign NGOs, mass organizations, and a combination of BEM throughout Indonesia (BEM-SI).<br><br>The following is the point of the Laznas Command Post for the Da'wah Care of the Sunda Strait in Banten and South Lampung:<br>
1). Cigeulis Village Combined Post, District Cigeulis, Pandeglang.<br>
2). Al Anshor Training Center for Da'wah Council Jl Cibaru Jaha, Cisiram Village, Chicken Mine Ds, Anyer, Serang District.<br>
3). Kp. Joint Post Legon, Sumberjaya Village, Kec. Sumur, Kab. Pandeglang.<br>
4). Nurul Hikmah Islamic Boarding School, Kertajaya Village, Kec. Sumur, Kab. Pandeglang.<br>
5). Hot Water Village, Kalianda District, South Lampung.<br>
6). Desa Way Muli, Kec Kalianda, South Lampung.<br>
7). Village appeal, Kalianda district, South Lampung.<br><br>
Be one of the millions of goodness that comes in to help the Sunda Strait refugees face post-disaster difficulties!</article>
